After reviewing the retrieved evidence, what is your updated stance on whether the type of remission after a major depressive episode is an important risk factor for relapses in a 4-year follow-up?
Answer with at most 2 sentences. Then state your clear choice using \boxed{{letter}}
Based on the retrieved evidence, the type of remission significantly affects long-term relapse risk: patients achieving complete remission exhibit markedly lower relapse rates (e.g., 15.18%) compared to those with partial remission (67.6%), particularly evident in longitudinal studies tracking outcomes over multiyear intervals. This difference persists despite variations in initial severity or treatment approach, reinforcing the predictive value of remission completeness. \boxed{\text{A}}

